= Negotiations, Pt. 3

The details of a cabinet headed by [+ nsdap_chancellor +] have begun to take final shape, and Hindenburg took a major step in that direction by summoning General Werner von Blomberg to Berlin to be available to succeed Schleicher as Defense Minister. Hindenburg believed that he had selected an apolitical, professional officer, but he had instead chosen a man highly susceptible to the allures of <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazism</span>.

Meanwhile, [+ nsdap_chancellor +] gave in to Hindenburg's insistence that Papen become [? if prussia_leader == "Schleicher": both the Minister-President of Prussia and?] the Vice Chancellor, leading to Papen approving Wilhelm Frick's appointment to the national Interior Ministry, and Göring to the Prussian one. [+ nsdap_leader +] then introduced a new demand: the dissolution of the Reichstag so a new election could be held. And as Chancellor, he would also require the passage of an "enabling act", centralizing authority in the cabinet.

Papen raised no objections to this new demand, although Hugenberg may raise his concerns in an upcoming meeting to secure his participation in the cabinet.

